        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-10T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="480" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.34/6–1047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-10T14:00:00-04:00">June 10, 1947—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>461. 1. Military Air Attaché approached Chilean authorities re possible
                    acquisition vessels mentioned <gloss target="#t_Depgam1">Depgam</gloss> 177 May
                    7. Chileans interested but unable discuss details at moment (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 266 June 4<note n="44" xml:id="d480fn1">Not printed.</note>).</p>
                <p>2. Chief Naval Mission<note n="45" xml:id="d480fn2">Capt. Oberlin C.
                        Laird.</note> states vessels are scattered along Chilean coast and strongly
                    recommends their remaining Chilean custody pending negotiations; mission lacks
                    funds or personnel properly safeguard vessels if possession taken.</p>
                <p>3. Embassy reluctant press negotiations re vessels pending completion
                    arrangements sale aircraft mentioned <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                    403 May 26.<note n="46" xml:id="d480fn3">Not printed, but see <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Please advise status aircraft deal and expedite
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
